race.comment: Tricky race to kick off the card with a couple of these facing the starter for the first time. Of the raced brigade BOOM BREAK (1) is unlucky to still be a maiden hitting the top-four in all five starts to date and strikes a winnable contest here. Finished runner-up over this track and trip when resuming and gets the reliable Gollan/Lang combination. Rates the testing material. LUKEY BLUE (13) was a touch disappointing last time out but go on the solid second here two back. Can bounce right back in a field decimated by scratchings. ZEMOREYA (6) is on debut but has showed ability at the trials and is sure to be well-educated out of the Archibald camp. Respect any market push. SHAQUE D'AMOUR (17) next in line.
